 succeeded in 0ms:
     1	# Stage 2 Frames and State
     2	
     3	This document defines the stage-2 state aggregation boundary for UAV, arm, and
     4	future vision state.
     5	
     6	## State Aggregator
     7	
     8	Run:
     9	
    10	```bash
    11	ros2 run aerial_manip_control state_aggregator
    12	```
    13	
    14	The node consumes only high-level state topics:
    15	
    16	| Topic | Direction | Type | Notes |
    17	| --- | --- | --- | --- |
    18	| `/uav/current_position` | subscribe | `geometry_msgs/msg/PointStamped` | Existing UAV bridge output in local PX4 NED. |
    19	| `/uav/control_state` | subscribe | `std_msgs/msg/String` | Existing UAV bridge state. |
    20	| `/arm/current_joint_state` | subscribe | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/ArmState` | Arm bridge/controller state. |
    21	| `/arm/control_state` | subscribe | `std_msgs/msg/String` | Arm bridge state. |
    22	| `/system/observation` | publish | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/SystemObservation` | Combined platform and arm observation. |
    23	| `/system/safety_status` | publish | `aerial_manip_msgs/msg/SafetyStatus` | Aggregated freshness and bridge-state health. |
    24	
    25	The aggregator does not publish to `/uav/*` and does not change `/uav/*`
    26	topic semantics.
    27	
    28	## TF Tree
    29	
    30	The intended baseline TF tree is:
    31	
    32	```text
    33	map -> uav/base_link -> uav/arm_base -> uav/ee_link -> uav/camera_link
    34	```
    35	
    36	`state_aggregator` broadcasts this tree. `map` is the ROS ENU world frame.
    37	`uav/base_link`, `uav/arm_base`, `uav/ee_link`, and `uav/camera_link` are FLU
    38	body/link frames unless a later robot description provides more specific link
    39	conventions.
    40	
    41	Default fixed offsets:
    42	
    43	| Transform | Default translation |
    44	| --- | --- |
    45	| `uav/base_link -> uav/arm_base` | `[0.0, 0.0, -0.08]` |
    46	| `uav/ee_link -> uav/camera_link` | `[0.12, 0.0, -0.04]` |
    47	
    48	These are parameters and should be replaced by URDF-derived transforms when the
    49	stage-2 model package owns a complete robot description.
    50	
    51	## Coordinate Boundary
    52	
    53	`/uav/current_position` remains local PX4 NED:
    54	
    55	```text
    56	x = north, y = east, z = down
    57	```
    58	
    59	`/system/observation.platform.position_ned` preserves that NED value exactly so
    60	downstream modules can inspect the original bridge state without ambiguity.
    61	
    62	The only baseline conversion performed by `state_aggregator` is for TF:
    63	
    64	```text
    65	enu_x = ned_y
    66	enu_y = ned_x
    67	enu_z = -ned_z
    68	```
    69	
    70	This keeps NED/ENU conversion centralized at the system observation boundary
    71	while leaving existing UAV bridge topics unchanged. The current baseline does
    72	not yet consume UAV attitude, so `map -> uav/base_link` uses identity rotation.
    73	When attitude is added, FRD-to-FLU conversion should be added in this node or
    74	the existing UAV bridge, not in external vision, policy, or LeRobot modules.
    75	
    76	## Safety Status
    77	
    78	`/system/safety_status` reports:
    79	
    80	- `safe=true`, `severity=SEVERITY_OK`, `state=OK` when recent UAV and arm state
    81	  are available and neither bridge reports `INVALID_TARGET`.
    82	- `safe=false`, `severity=SEVERITY_WARN`, `state=DEGRADED` when UAV or arm state
    83	  is missing/stale or a bridge reports `INVALID_TARGET`.
    84	
    85	The `state_timeout` parameter controls stale-state detection. The default is
    86	`1.0` second.

